                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13289446" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 14:12:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch implementing the syntax in the description.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13289475" author="jkrupan" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 15:15:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To be clear, the intent is that the value of a &quot;delete&quot; can be an array which contains a list of zero or more id&apos;s to be deleted. At first I thought it was a range (start and end), but in fact it is a list of specific id&apos;s.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I presume that somebody will update the doc as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13289476" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 15:16:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While I&apos;m in here mucking with the delete syntax, we should probably have a way to specify the version of deletes in the body of the update request as well (as opposed to a param on the URL).  It should prob just sit right beside the current &quot;commitWithin&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13289549" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 17:25:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that allows the specification of &lt;em&gt;version&lt;/em&gt; along with each delete.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
